snippet.textDisplay:
When you read the comments, all the hate towards JLo comes from people from South America. I understand Shakira is from your country/continent, but come on. You can't underestimate someone just because she is from the caribbean (Puerto Rico). They are two types of latinas with two TOTALLY different styles and they were both absolutely STUNNING. The most objective comments I've read come from the American audience, due to them being "non-biased".

Jlo wanted to give a messege to the USA in defense of the immigrants from Center and South America. That they are important and should have the same rights. Puertoricans are not immigrants, yet she stood up for the people that are not even from her country. That's what people who criticize her still don't seem to acknowledge. ¿Así o más claro?
